Details of the current API: 
(The plugin is currently in an early development stage, so the documenation will be improved in the future!)

<ip> -> the ip address of your vdr
<port> -> currently 8002

TIMERS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/timers?/.json

RECORDINGS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/recordings?/.json

EVENTS/EPG:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events?/<channel>/.json
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events?/<channel>/<duration>/.json
GET http://<ip>:<port>/events?/<channel>/<duration>/<from>/.json
<channel> is the number of your channel
<duration> duration of the time period in seconds from which you want to know the event details
<from> start of the time period

CHANNELS:
GET http://<ip>:<port>/channels?/.json
